  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Peacebuilding in the North-Eastern Border Area of C&#xF4;te d&apos;Ivoire, Through Participatory and Planned Management of Natural Resources</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to reduce community conflicts related to the competition between different groups - including indigenous and migrant communities - for the exploitation and control of land and natural resources in the north-eastern part of C&#xF4;te d&apos;Ivoire in the border region with Burkina Faso. Activities include the establishment of participatory and inclusive natural resource management mechanisms, the strengthening of dialogue with local authorities and the development of viable economic alternatives that ensure the sustainable use of natural resources necessary for the communities&apos; resilience to climate change. In the absence of effective mechanisms for dialogue and sustainable economic opportunities, these conflicts can increase with the movement of people linked to climate change related disruptions in production systems, as well as increase the risk of the spread of extremism from neighbouring countries.</narrative>
  </description>
